# Build output — generated by tsup on `pnpm install` (prepare script).
# Keeping dist/ out of git eliminates 100+ generated files from every
# diff and stops rebases from drowning in artifact-rename conflicts.
# Consumer behaviour unchanged: when someone runs `pnpm install` against
# a tagged commit, the prepare script runs `tsup` if dist/ is missing,
# producing the same dist/ that used to be committed.
dist/
